Limited data on outcomes of pregnancies that have occurred following eculizumab use in pregnant women have not identified a concern for specific adverse developmental outcomes (see Data). There are risks to the mother and fetus associated with untreated paroxysmal nocturnal hemoglobinuria (PNH) and atypical hemolytic uremic syndrome (aHUS) in pregnancy (see Clinical Considerations
                                 ). Animal studies using a mouse analogue of the eculizumab molecule (murine anti-C5 antibody) showed increased rates of developmental abnormalities and an increased rate of dead and moribund offspring at doses 2-8 times the human dose (see Data
                                 ).
